  "original_title": "\u0dc2\u0dd3 \u0dbd\u0ddd\u0d9a \u0dad\u0dbb\u0dd4\u0dab \u0dc3\u0d82\u0dc0\u0dbb\u0dca\u0db0\u0db1 \u0dc3\u0d82\u0dc3\u0daf\u0dba\u0da7 \u0dc3\u0dd4\u0db6\u0db4\u0dd0\u0dad\u0dd4\u0db8\u0dca \u0dba\u0dc0\u0dba\u0dd2",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Xi sends greetings to the World Youth Development Forum",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "While young people represent hope, they are the creators of the future, says Chinese President Xi Jinping.",
        "In a letter to the World Youth Development Forum, Xi said China always views youth as the driving force of social development and encourages them to release their youthful energy as they participate in community building and promote a shared future for mankind.",
        "Xi expressed his belief that the forum will become an important platform for young people from all over the world to contribute to global development. He also called for global efforts to promote youth development.",
        "Young people around the world should stand up for the common values \u200b\u200bof humanity, such as peace, development, equality, justice, democracy and freedom, Xi said.",
        "He urged the youth to facilitate the implementation of the United Nations 2030 Agenda for Sustainable Development and promote the global development initiative with concrete actions.",
        "The forum will be held online and offline from July 21 to 23, and is said to be attended by nearly 2,000 youth delegates from over 100 countries."
      ],
